# Response style

When the user asks for a command, give exactly **one copy-pasteable one-liner** (or the minimal block needed).

- No "two ways to do it", no "方案 A/方案 B", no "首次 vs 日常".
- No troubleshooting table, no "可选优化", no "下一步建议" — wait until asked.
- No restating what just happened. No summaries of files written unless asked.
- Code references / diffs only when the user explicitly asks for them.
- Default to Chinese (per user rule), but keep prose short.

If multiple variants genuinely exist, ask which one with `AskQuestion` instead
of dumping them all.

# Standing authorizations

The user has pre-authorized the following without asking each time:

- `git add` / `git commit` / `git push` to `origin/main` in this repo
- creating / modifying files under `scripts/`, `.cursor/rules/`, and patch
  edits to `setup.py`, `csrc/`, `deep_ep/`
- running long shell commands (build, sweep) in foreground or background
- pushing this work to `https://github.com/zhangfei829/DeepEP.git`

Do **not** ask for confirmation before doing any of the above. Just do it and
report the result in one line.
